bn: do yegla islands

The Ghesites have domesticated horses to use as mounts - interestingly, not used also for work as beasts of burden. Rather than focusing on breeding a specific breed, they focus instead on individual utility and abilities of horses, breeding them across breeds to maximise speed, agility, and stamina. Culturally, the Ghesites possess strong companionship towards their mounts, a relationship somewhere between a pet and a companion (but not a family/clan member). There is also a stigma around eating horse meat, partly due to this companionship, and partly due to practicality surrounding the utility of horse mounts.

Yegla Islands wrote:A unified South America is actually the primary superpower of their canon, and is regarded with envy by both the United States and Russia (who have banded together into a sort of cursed axis based on a desire to become great again). I'll admit, it's a novel take.

The Islands maintain a mainland colony, which operates semi-autonomously from the Islands though remain on a tight leash held by the United Yeglan Party. It's mostly allowed to play around with its own domestic policies, though the interests of the Islands in terms of a buffer state and military prowess always come first. The protectorate is one of three national states friendly towards the Islands.
